         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>l. 3: The addition of Augustus lengthens the line surprisingly but seems necessary unless perhaps AVG in line  10 should be read AVGG - but that too would be unsual </p>
            <p>l. 10: The young Philip became cos on 1st Jan. 247, Augustus in August 246 and cos II on 1st Jan. 248; Assuming the text to have been drafted accurately it must belong to the second half of 247.</p>
